Why I reject the AC/DC High Voltage CD:
- Production aesthetic mismatch: High Voltage’s minimal studio polish and raw, gritty guitar‑forward production conflict with my preference for pristine, multi‑layered, high‑production studio statements. While I do value guitar‑forward classic rock, I specifically prize warm, polished AOR productions; AC/DC’s intentionally rough, live‑feel grit trades off the polished midrange and orchestral/cinematic lift I seek.
